---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does a new hot water system cost in Pakenham in 2026?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Fitted prices in Pakenham and Cardinia in 2026: a gas or electric storage unit $1,400-$2,600, a continuous-flow gas unit $1,800-$2,900, and a heat-pump unit $2,800-$4,500 before rebates (the federal and Victorian rebates can take a chunk off a heat pump). Worked example: a Cardinia Lakes family replacing a dead 12-year-old gas storage unit like-for-like usually pays around $2,100 same-day, including removal of the old unit, the new Rheem or Rinnai unit, a tempering valve, fittings and a Certificate of Compliance." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My hot water unit died &mdash; can you replace it same day?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Usually yes. We carry and can source the common Rheem, Rinnai, Dux and Aquamax gas, electric, heat-pump and solar units, so a like-for-like changeover can often be done the same day &mdash; important when a Pakenham family has no hot water on a cold morning. We remove the old unit, install the new one to AS/NZS 3500, fit a compliant tempering valve, and issue a Certificate of Compliance." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long should a hot water system last?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Gas and electric storage units typically last 10-15 years, continuous-flow gas a little longer, and heat pumps around 10-15 years. The original units in the early-2000s Cardinia Lakes, Lakeside and Heritage Springs estates are now in that replacement window, which is why we see them failing in batches. Signs yours is going: rusty or discoloured hot water, water pooling under the tank, knocking noises, or running cold faster than it used to." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Should I switch from gas to a heat pump in Pakenham?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "For many Cardinia homes a heat-pump hot water system is the cheapest to run, and the federal and Victorian rebates reduce the upfront cost. A heat pump suits a home with daytime solar especially well. That said, a like-for-like gas changeover is cheaper upfront and faster in an emergency. We will give you both numbers honestly at the quote so you can choose &mdash; and either way you get a Certificate of Compliance." }
    }
  ]
};
---
<Layout
  title="Hot Water Systems Pakenham | Repair &amp; Replace, Same Day | (03) 9003 0108"
  canonical="https://pakenhamplumbers.com.au/services/hot-water-systems/"
  description="Hot water repair &amp; replacement for Pakenham, Cardinia Lakes &amp; Cardinia Shire &mdash; gas, electric, heat-pump &amp; solar. Rheem, Rinnai, Dux, Aquamax. Same-day changeover, tempering valve &amp; Certificate of Compliance. From $1,400 fitted.">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Same-day repair &amp; replacement</span>
      <h1>Hot water systems in <span class="accent">Pakenham &amp; Cardinia</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        No hot water? We repair and replace gas, electric, heat-pump and solar hot water
        &mdash; Rheem, Rinnai, Dux, Aquamax. Most failures are a same-day fix or
        like-for-like changeover, with a tempering valve and Certificate of Compliance.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Repair, replace or upgrade.</h2>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">

        <h3>Repairs &mdash; often a same-day fix.</h3>
        <p>
          Not every dead hot water unit needs replacing. A tripped or burnt-out element,
          a failed thermocouple or gas valve, a stuck tempering valve or a leaking relief
          valve are common, repairable faults. We diagnose first and tell you honestly
          whether a repair makes sense or whether the unit is at end of life. No hot water
          on a cold Cardinia morning is treated as an
          <a href="/services/emergency-plumber/">emergency</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Replacement &mdash; the four system types.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Gas storage</strong> &mdash; the Cardinia default. Reliable, good recovery, $1,400&ndash;$2,600 fitted. Rheem, Rinnai, Dux.</li>
          <li><strong>Continuous-flow gas</strong> &mdash; endless hot water, compact, wall-mounted. $1,800&ndash;$2,900 fitted. Rinnai Infinity, Rheem Metro.</li>
          <li><strong>Electric storage</strong> &mdash; simple, cheap to buy, best on off-peak or with solar. $1,400&ndash;$2,400 fitted.</li>
          <li><strong>Heat pump</strong> &mdash; cheapest to run, rebate-eligible. $2,800&ndash;$4,500 before rebates. Excellent with daytime solar.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">When to replace, not repair.</h3>
        <p>
          Storage units last <strong>10&ndash;15 years</strong> &mdash; exactly the window
          the original Cardinia Lakes, Lakeside and Heritage Springs estate units are now
          in, which is why we see them failing in batches. Replace when you see rusty or
          discoloured hot water, water pooling under the tank, knocking, or the unit
          running cold faster than it used to. A leaking tank cannot be repaired &mdash;
          once the inner cylinder corrodes through, the unit is done.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Worked example.</h3>
        <p>
          A Cardinia Lakes family replacing a dead 12-year-old gas storage unit
          like-for-like usually pays around <strong>$2,100</strong> done same-day &mdash;
          that covers removal of the old unit, the new Rheem or Rinnai unit, a compliant
          tempering valve (mandatory for delivered-water temperature), fittings and a
          Certificate of Compliance. We install to <strong>AS/NZS 3500</strong>, and where
          a gas unit is involved, to <strong>AS/NZS 5601</strong> with a CoC.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Rebates &amp; running cost.</h3>
        <p>
          Federal and Victorian rebates can take a meaningful chunk off a heat-pump
          changeover, and a heat pump paired with daytime solar is the cheapest hot water
          to run in most Cardinia homes. We will quote both a like-for-like gas option and
          a heat-pump option so you can compare upfront cost against running cost honestly.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Where we work.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-lakes/">Cardinia Lakes</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/lakeside/">Lakeside</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/heritage-springs/">Heritage Springs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/officer/">Officer</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/beaconsfield/">Beaconsfield</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-shire/">All Cardinia Shire</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>No hot water in Pakenham?</h2>
        <p>Same-day repair or replacement. Gas, electric, heat-pump, solar. CoC included.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
